			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://blog.hafchurch.org/peter/wp-content/uploads/clocks.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-298" title="It's Time!" src="http://blog.hafchurch.org/peter/wp-content/uploads/clocks.jpg" alt="" width="156" height="160" /></a>The time for talking is over. The time for action is now!</p>
<p>On my journey to rediscover <em>who</em> the Church are, I am finding that I am also rediscovering <em>what</em> the Church is or more specifically <em>how</em> the Church should act.</p>
<p>I could list the scriptures here if you want but I won&#8217;t. They are right there unavoidably obvious in your bible and you read them time and time again.</p>
<p>Here&#8217;s just one of the many:</p>
<blockquote><p>Luke 9:23-25 Then he said to them all: &#8220;If anyone  would come after me, he must deny himself and take up his cross daily and follow  me. For whoever wants to save his life  will lose it, but whoever loses his life for me will save it. What good is it for a man to gain the whole world, and  yet lose or forfeit his very self?</p></blockquote>
<p>So I have been thinking&#8230; what can I do? What can WE do? How do we step outside of the bounds of our lives today and live sacrificial lives? How do we die to ourselves? What can we actually <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>DO</em></span> rather than what can we just talk about?</p>
<p>So I have a plan, a challenge, an opportunity for you all.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s called the 12 Days of Christmas Challenge&#8230;.</p>
<p>and here&#8217;s the first part of the challenge:</p>
<p>Will you pray about whether or not God wants you to take up the 12 Days of Christmas Challenge <strong>before</strong> you know what the challenge is?</p>
<p>Will you ask Him &#8220;Lord, is it your will for me to take up the challenge?&#8221; and will you do it if He answers yes?</p>
<p>Without knowing what the challenge is, are you prepared to commit to something just because God says He wants you to?</p>
<p>Are you willing to put aside all human reason and questions and simply respond in faith?</p>
<p>Will you pray about it tonight?</p>
]]></content:encoded>
